f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Kafkai is best suited for niche SEO content, automated blogging, content farms, bulk articles, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Surfer, meanwhile, shines for SEO optimization, content scoring, keyword research, content strategy, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2019, Kafkai describes itself as \"Niche-trained AI writer for automated SEO content.\" Surfer, established in 2017, positions itself as \"Data-driven SEO content optimization and writing platform.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Surfer** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 4.0), more features (6 vs 4). However, this does not mean Kafkai is a poor choice — far from it. Kafkai excels in its own right, particularly for niche SEO content and automated blogging.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best-in-class content scoring against serp competitors, go with Surfer. If pre-trained models for specific niches matters more to you, Kafkai is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
